'''"As it were"''' is a parenthetic [[phrase]] used to indicate that a word or statement is perhaps not formally exact though practically right. The phrase is likely a truncation of "as it were so".
==Equivalences==
*"so to speak"
*"In a manner of speaking"
*"as if it were"
*"as if such were so"
*"in a way"
